timing_disable..._box_endpoints(25.10)  timing_disable..._box_endpoints(25.10)

Name
       timing_disable_black_box_endpoints

Syntax
       timing_disable_black_box_endpoints {true | false}

       Default: false

       Ignores any boundary model endpoints on black box instances.

       When  set  to  false,  the fanout logic from the block's input ports is
       traced for storing as timed logic within the boundary model. If  a  pin
       is reached with no outgoing timing arcs, this is considered an endpoint
       of  the  model  and  the fanin to that endpoint will be included in the
       model.

       When set to true, such pins are ignored when  they  are  on  cells  for
       which  no timing or LEF cell definition was loaded. This is intended to
       make the model generation more tolerant of missing libraries  in  cases
       where the power/ground connectivity is included in the netlist.

       To set this global variable, use the set command.

